subject: Changes to accept dump object path after createDump call
commitMessage:
Changes to accept dump object path after createDump call

This commit contains changes to accept the object path instead
of the dump Id for user-initiated dumps.

Earlier a task would be started to monitor the 'interfaces added'
signal when a new dump object is created. Now, the 'Status' property
will be checked for the completion of dump creation.

And the createDump dbus call has been changed in the backend to accept
additional arguments. The changes for the same has been added in this
commit (w.r.t the following commits):

https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/36331
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/+/37792

With this change failed dumps will now be returning an internal
error back to the user, as a part of the task message.

Latest change in createdump call:
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/44380

One more change added is:
Increased the task timer to 6 minutes. Observed that the bmc dumps
are taking a bit longer than 3 minutes while ipling and the task timer expires
with task state set to cancelled. Hence the change.
